gt.blockmachines.algaefarm.controller.tier.single.tooltip=Machine Type: §eAlgae Pond§r\n§4DEPRECATED - Controller will be removed in next major update!\n§4Check NEI for new Controller and conversion recipe\nGrows Algae!\nProvide compost to boost production by one tier\nDoes not require power or maintenance\nAll Machine Casings must be the same tier, this dictates machine speed\nFill Input Hatch with Water to fill the inside of the multiblock\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
gt.blockmachines.algaefarm.controller.tier.single.tooltip.15545=Machine Type: §eAlgae Pond§r\nGrows Algae!\nProvide compost to boost production by one tier\nMachine tier is equal to the highest energy hatch tier, capped by glass tier\n§c§l§nUMV§r§7-glass unlocks all above energy tiers\nAccepts exactly 1 Energy Hatch\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines\nStructure by: §a§6IX§r§7
gt.blockmachines.algaefarm.controller.tier.single.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §69§7x§63§7x§69§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) §c(Hollow)\n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front bottom center\n§6   75x §r§7Machine Casing (minimum) (tiered)\n§6   64x §r§7Sterile Farm Casing\n§f   Input Bus: §7Any Casing\n§f   Output Bus: §7Any Casing\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Any Casing\n   Uses sub channel §6casing§r§7 for §6Machine Casing Tier\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
gt.blockmachines.algaefarm.controller.tier.single.tooltip_secondary.15545=§fDimensions: §63§7x§66§7x§610§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front center, 3rd layer\n§6   20x §r§7Algae Casing (minimum)\n§6   6x §r§7Stainless Steel Frame Box\n§6   64x §r§7Any Tiered Glass (tiered)\n§f   Input Bus: §7Any Casing\n§f   Output Bus: §7Any Casing\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Any Casing\n§f   Energy Hatch: §7Any Casing\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7Any Casing\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
gt.blockmachines.amazonprime.controller.tier.single.name=Amazon Warehousing Depot
gt.blockmachines.amazonprime.controller.tier.single.tooltip=Machine Type: §ePackager, Unpackager, AWD§r\n§4DEPRECATED - Controller will be removed in next major update!\n§4Check NEI for new Controller and conversion recipe\nThis Multiblock is used for EXTREME packaging requirements\n§616§7 Parallels per §fVoltage§7 Tier\n§a600%§7 Speed\n§b75%§7 EU Usage\nCan be configured with a screwdriver to work as an Unpackager\nDust Schematics are inserted into the input buses\nIf inserted into the controller, it is shared across all buses\n1x, 2x, 3x & Other Schematics are to be placed into the controller GUI slot\n§540 §7Pollution per second\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
gt.blockmachines.amazonprime.controller.tier.single.tooltip.15513=Machine Type: §ePackager, Unpackager, AWD§r\nThis Multiblock is used for EXTREME packaging requirements\nCan be configured to work as an Unpackager in controller\n§616§7 Parallels per §fVoltage§7 Tier\n§a+100%§7 Speed per §fItem Pipe Casing§7 Tier\n§b75%§7 EU Usage\n§540 §7Pollution per second\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines\nStructure by: §a§6Oasis_Cactus§r§7
gt.blockmachines.amazonprime.controller.tier.single.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §63§7x§63§7x§63§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) §c(Hollow)\n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front center\n§6   10x §r§7Supply Depot Casing (minimum)\n§f   Input Bus: §7Any Casing\n§f   Output Bus: §7Any Casing\n§f   Energy Hatch: §7Any Casing\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7Any Casing\n§f   Muffler Hatch: §7Any Casing\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
gt.blockmachines.amazonprime.controller.tier.single.tooltip_secondary.15513=§fDimensions: §65§7x§63§7x§63§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) §c(Hollow)\n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front right, 2nd layer\n§6   4x §r§7Supply Depot Casing (minimum)\n§6   3x §r§7Item Pipe (tiered)\n§6   2x §r§7Iron Frame Box\n§6   3x §r§7Any Tiered Glass (tiered)\n§f   Input Bus: §7Any Casing\n§f   Output Bus: §7Any Casing\n§f   Energy Hatch: §7Any Casing\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7Any Casing\n§f   Muffler Hatch: §7Any Casing\n   Uses sub channel §6glass§r§7 for §6Glass Tier\n   Uses sub channel §6item_pipe§r§7 for §6Item Pipe Casing Tier\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
gt.blockmachines.antimatterforge.name=Semi-Stable Antimatter Stabilization Sequencer
gt.blockmachines.antimatterforge.tooltip=Machine Type: §eAntimatter Forge, SSASS§r\n§dDimensions not included!§7\nConverts protomatter into antimatter\nUse screwdriver to disable rendering\nPassively consumes 10,000,000 + (§3Antimatter§7 * 1000)^(1.5 - §a§l§nM§r§7) EU/t\nThe consumption decays by 0.5% every tick when empty\nActively uses (§3Antimatter§7 * 10,000)^(1.5 - §5§l§nG§r§7) EU per cycle to produce antimatter\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nCycles every second\nEvery cycle, the lowest amount of antimatter in the 16 antimatter hatches is recorded\nAll hatches with more than the lowest amount §close half the difference!§7\n§cVoids 10% of antimatter §7if it runs out of energy/protomatter during a cycle\nBase production per hatch is (1/16) * (§3Antimatter§7^(0.5 + §6§l§nC§r§7)) of antimatter each cycle\nEach hatch multiplies the base production per hatch with a random number pulled from\na normal distribution with a mean of 0.2 + §b§l§nA§r§7 and a variance of 1\nThe total gain of antimatter can be negative!\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nCan be supplied with stabilization fluids to improve antimatter generation\nEach stabilization can only use one of the fluids at a time\n§a§l§nM§r§aagnetic Stabilization§7 (Consumes §3Antimatter§7^0.5 L of fluid per cycle)\n1. Molten Purified Tengam = §a0.1§7\n2. Tachyon Rich Fluid = §a0.2§7\n3. Molten MagMatter = §a0.3§7\n§5§l§nG§r§5ravity Stabilization§7 (Consumes §3Antimatter§7^0.5 L of fluid per cycle)\n1. Molten Spacetime = §50.05§7\n2. Spatially Enlarged Fluid = §50.10§7\n3. Molten Eternity = §50.15§7\n§6§l§nC§r§6ontainment Stabilization§7 (Consumes §3Antimatter§7^(2/7) L of fluid per cycle)\n1. Molten Shirabon = §60.05§7\n2. Molten MHDCSM = §60.10§7\n§b§l§nA§r§bctivation Stabilization§7 (Consumes §3Antimatter§7^(1/3) L of fluid per cycle)\n1. Depleted Naquadah Fuel Mk V = §b0.05§7\n2. Depleted Naquadah Fuel Mk VI = §b0.10§7\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
gt.blockmachines.antimatterforge.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §653§7x§653§7x§647§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front center\n§6   512x §r§7Antimatter Containment Casing (minimum)\n§6   2274x §r§7Magnetic Flux Casing (minimum)\n§6   623x §r§7Gravity Stabilization Casing (minimum)\n§6   126x §r§7Protomatter Activation Coil (minimum)\n§f   Input Hatch: §71-6, Hint block number 1\n§f   Energy Hatch: §71-9, Hint block number 2\n§f   Antimatter Hatch: §716, Hint block number 3\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
gt.blockmachines.antimattergenerator.name=Shielded Lagrangian Annihilation Matrix
gt.blockmachines.antimattergenerator.tooltip=Machine Type: §eAntimatter Generator, SLAM§r\nAnnihilating Antimatter like it's 2205!\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nGenerates energy by reacting §bSemi-Stable Antimatter§7 with §6Matter\nAnnihilation uses an equal amount of §bAntimatter§7 and §6Matter\nConsumes §6all inputs§7 every processing cycle\n§cVoids any invalid fluid!\nA cycle lasts 5 seconds\nAn imbalance between §bAntimatter§7 and §6Matter§c decreases efficiency!§7\nEfficiency formula: Min(§bAntimatter§7/§6Matter§7, §6Matter§7/§bAntimatter§7)\nAny excess EU generated will be §cvoided!§7\nCannot produce more than §a9.22e18§7 EU per cycle\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nEnergy production formula: §a§l§nA§r§7 * (§bAntimatter§7 ^ §6§l§nE§r§7) EU/Cycle\n§a§l§nA§r§antimatter energy§7 base value: §a1.00e12§7 EU/L\n§6§l§nE§r§6nergy production boost§r§7:\n1. Molten Copper: §61.00\n2. Molten Superconductor Base UIV: §61.02\n3. Molten Superconductor Base UMV: §61.03\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nSwitch the power destination to your wireless network with a screwdriver\nWireless mode requires Superconductor Base UMV to work\nWireless mode is still limited by hatch capacity\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
gt.blockmachines.antimattergenerator.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §635§7x§643§7x§635§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front center, 2nd layer\n§6   1008x §r§7Transcendentally Reinforced Borosilicate Glass (minimum)\n§6   4122x §r§7Magnetic Flux Casing (minimum)\n§6   2418x §r§7Gravity Stabilization Casing (minimum)\n§6   32x §r§7Protomatter Activation Coil (minimum)\n§6   600x §r§7Antimatter Annihilation Matrix (minimum)\n§6   293x §r§7Naquadria Frame Box (minimum)\n§6   209x §r§7Advanced Filter Casing (minimum)\n§f   Input Hatch: §72, Hint block number 1\n§f   Laser Source Hatch: §71-64, Hint block number 2\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
