gt.blockmachines.ggfab.machine.adv_assline.name=Advanced Assembly Line
gt.blockmachines.ggfab.machine.adv_assline.tooltip=Machine Type: §eAssembly Line, AAL§r\nAssembly Line with item pipelining\nAll fluids are consumed at the start of the recipe\nRecipe tier is limited by the lowest Energy Hatch tier\n§6§m-------------------------------------------------------------------\nRuns imperfect overclocks until Energy Hatch tier\nAdditional overclocks are increasingly more expensive\n§bMultiplier = 4^(Regular Overclocks) × 4.3 × 4.6 × … × (4 + 0.3 × Extra Overclocks)§7\n§bPower usage = Multiplier × (Active Slices) × (Recipe EU/t)§7\nOverclocking assumes all recipe slices are active\n§lDoes not overclock beyond 1 tick\n§6§m-------------------------------------------------------------------\nConstructed identically to the Assembly Line\n§aSupports TecTech Multi-Amp and Laser Hatches!\n§7§m-------------------------------------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
gt.blockmachines.ggfab.machine.adv_assline.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §65-16§7x§64§7x§63§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   From Bottom to Top, Left to Right\n   Layer 1 - Solid Steel Machine Casing, Input Bus, Solid Steel Machine Casing\n   Layer 2 - Glass, Assembly Line Casing, Glass\n   Layer 3 - Grate Machine Casing, Assembler Machine Casing, Grate Machine Casing\n   Layer 4 - Empty, Solid Steel Machine Casing, Empty\n   Up to 16 repeating slices, each one allows for 1 more item in recipes\n   §fController: §7Either Grate on layer 3 of the first slice\n§f   Energy Hatch: §7Any layer 4 casing\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7Any layer 1 casing\n§f   Input Bus: §7As specified on layer 1\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Any layer 1 casing\n§f   Output Bus: §7Replaces Input Bus or Solid Steel Machine Casing on layer 1 of last slice\n§f   Data Access Hatch: §7Any Grate Machine Casing NOT on the first slice\n   Uses sub channel §6glass§r§7 for §6Glass Tier\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
