gt.blockmachines.industrialarcfurnace.controller.tier.single.tooltip=Machine Type: §eArc Furnace, Plasma Arc Furnace, IAF§r\n§4DEPRECATED - CHECK NEI TO FIND NEW CONTROLLER\n§6Width * Voltage Tier§7 Parallels\n§68x§7 Parallels in Plasma Mode\n§a350%§7 Speed\n§8100%§7 EU Usage\nRight-click controller with a Screwdriver to change modes\nMax Size required to process Plasma recipes\n§52400 §7Pollution per second\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
gt.blockmachines.industrialarcfurnace.controller.tier.single.tooltip.15548=Machine Type: §eArc Furnace, IAF§r\nInsert electrode in the electrode hatch\nSpeed, Parallel, OC and power use depend on the electrode\nSome electrodes have special effects, check their tooltip\nBelow §c30§7% durability: §c5§7% chance for random arc surge\nBelow §c10§7% durability: §c2§7% chance to destroy items in the arc\nStartup: machine ignites the arc before processing\nStartup power: based on electrode startup surge and parallels\nShutdown: machine powers down the arc after work ends\n-------------------------------Blast mode----------------------------------\nProcesses EBF recipes at §c16§7x power cost\n--------------------------------Ore Mode----------------------------------\nQuickly process metallic ores!\nStartup time: §c10§7 seconds\nConsumes all ores and raw ores from input buses\nOnly furnace-smeltable ores, no blasting\nIf queued ore exceeds capacity, startup ends immediately\nIf no ores enter for §c5§7 ticks, startup ends immediately\nOutputs molten metals\nRight-click with Screwdriver to change mode\n§aSupports TecTech Multi-Amp Hatches!\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
