gt.blockmachines.lftr.controller.single.name=Thorium Reactor [LFTR]
gt.blockmachines.lftr.controller.single.tooltip=Machine Type: §eReactor§r\nController Block for the Liquid Fluoride Thorium Reactor\nProduces energy and new elements from Radioactive Beta Decay!\nInput LFTB and a molten salt as fuel, and match the 4 Buffered Dynamo Hatches:\nLFTR Fuel 1 (4 EV Hatches), LFTR Fuel 2 (4 IV Hatches), LFTR Fuel 3 (4 LuV Hatches)\nIf using better hatches for a worse fuel, only 1 hatch will output EU\nOutputs U233 every 10 seconds, on average, while the reactor is running\nCheck NEI to see the other 3 outputs - they differ between fuels\n§54000 §7Pollution per second\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
gt.blockmachines.lftr.controller.single.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §67§7x§64§7x§67§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) §c(Hollow)\n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front bottom center\n§6   27x §r§7Hastelloy-N Reactor Casing (minimum)\n§6   26x §r§7Reactor Shield Casing (minimum)\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Top or bottom layer edges\n§f   Output Hatch: §7Top or bottom layer edges\n§f   Dynamo Hatch: §7Top or bottom layer edges\n§f   Muffler Hatch: §7Top 3x3\n   All dynamos must be between EV and LuV tier.\n   All other hatches must be IV+ tier.\n   4x Output Hatches or 1x Output Hatch (ME), 1+ Input Hatches\n   4x Dynamo Hatches, 4x Mufflers\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
gt.blockmachines.linear_accelerator.name=Linear Accelerator
gt.blockmachines.linear_accelerator.tooltip=Machine Type: §eParticle Accelerator, LINAC§r\nAccelerates particle beams to higher energies by passing them through an electric field\nElectrically neutral §5particles§7 are therefore unaffected\nUse a §bportable scanner §7for info about the input/output of this multiblock\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nRequires §fLength * 1,000 mB/s§7 of §bcoolant§7 to run, returns as §chot coolant\n§bLiquid Oxygen§f: 90 K\n§bLiquid Nitrogen§f: 77 K\n§bCoolant§f: 60 K\n§bSuper Coolant§f: 1 K\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nIncreasing the length/power increases the §9Output Beam Energy§7 but decreases the §2Output Beam Focus\nPreserve §2Beam Focus§7 more effectively with lower temperature §bcoolant\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§9Output Beam Energy§f = max(§eV§f, 50) * 10^§eIE\nwhere §eV§f = 0.25 * (Length - 1) * cbrt(§3EU/t Provided§f)\nand §eIE§f = 1 + min(§9Input Beam Energy§f, 7500) / §9Max Particle Energy\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§2Output Beam Focus§f = (§2Input Beam Focus§f + §eMachine Focus§f)/2§7 if §2Input Beam Focus§f > §eMachine Focus\n§2Output Beam Focus§f = §2Input Beam Focus§f * §eMachine Focus§f/100§7 if §2Input Beam Focus§f <= §eMachine Focus\nwhere §eMachine Focus§f = min(90, max(5, (-0.9 * (Length-1) * 1.1^(0.2 * §bCoolant Temperature§f) + 110)))\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
gt.blockmachines.linear_accelerator.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §67§7x§67§7x§619-83§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front bottom center\n§6   325x§7 - §61285x §r§7Shielded Accelerator Casing\n§6   148x§7 - §6852x §r§7Coolant Delivery Casing\n§6   127x§7 - §6703x §r§7Shielded Accelerator Glass\n§6   56x§7 - §6312x §r§7Superconducting Coil Block\n§6   156x§7 - §6732x §r§7Electrode Casing\n§6   47x §r§7Grate Machine Casing\n§6   48x §r§7Any Tiered Glass (LuV+)\n§f   Energy Hatch: §7Hint block with number 1\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7Hint block with number 1\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Hint block with number 2\n§f   Output Hatch: §7Hint block with number 2\n§f   Beam Input Hatch: §7Hint block with number 3\n§f   Beam Output Hatch: §7Hint block with number 4\n   Uses sub channel §6glass§r§7 for §6Glass Tier\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
