gt.blockmachines.multi.bec.io-node.tooltip=Machine Type: §eBEC I/O Node, Input Bus, Output Bus§r\n§7Teleports items into and out of the §6Bose-Einstein Condensate Observation Array§6§7.\n§7Recipe logic is the same as all other multiblocks.\n§7Condensate does not have to be present for a recipe to start.\n§7Right-click the controller with a programmed data stick to link it to the observation array.\n§7§8§m-----------------------------------------§8§7\n§7Each item slot in a recipe has an associated nanite tier.\n§7For the teleportation node to progress through an item slot, it must receive a nanite with the same or higher tier.\n§7Excess nanites linearly increase the speed at which recipes are crafted.\n§7This multiblock's EU/t remains constant even when it is paused, stalled, or slowed down.\n§7Each recipe crafted in parallel increases the EU/t consumed linearly.\n§7This multiblock does not overclock.\n§7§8§m-----------------------------------------§8§7\n§7The min and max parallels can be configured in the parameters to guarantee exact recipe timings.\n§7Recipes can be forcefully slowed down to compensate for slow automation by the §6Speed Divisor§6§7 parameter.\n§7§8§m-----------------------------------------§8§7\n§7The §6Nanite Detector Hatch§6§7 can be used to detect the teleportation node's requested nanites.\n§7The §6Teleportation Node Controller Hatch§6§7 can be used to temporarily pause the teleportation node.\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines\nAdded by: §a§9Recursive Pineapple§r§7
gt.blockmachines.multi.bec.io-node.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §67§7x§623§7x§613§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n§6   94x §r§7Coherence-Preserving Plasma Conduit\n§6   -14x§7 - §650x §r§7Electromagnetically-Isolated Casing\n§6   45x §r§7Fine-Structure Constant Manipulator\n§6   88x §r§7Conflict Inducement Casing\n§6   32x §r§7Peace Enforcement Casing\n§6   44x §r§7Condensate Transformative Coil\n§6   20x §r§7Condensate Guidance Coil\n§6   56x §r§7Electromagnetic Waveguide\n§f   Input Bus: §7Any Electromagnetically-Isolated Casing (Hint: 1)\n§f   Output Bus: §7Any Electromagnetically-Isolated Casing (Hint: 1)\n§f   Nanite Detector Hatch: §7Any Electromagnetically-Isolated Casing (Hint: 1)\n§f   Teleportation Node Controller Hatch: §7Any Electromagnetically-Isolated Casing (Hint: 1)\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
gt.blockmachines.multi.bec.storage.tooltip=Machine Type: §eBEC Storage, Entangled Condensate Storage§r\n§7Contained condensate is exposed to all observation arrays on the current network.\n§7Condensate routing can be controlled by using a §6Bose-Einstein Condensate Maxwell Gate§6§7.\n§7§8§m-----------------------------------------§8§7\n§7Storage capacity is controlled by the field strength.\n§7The field strength is configurable in the UI. It can also be set by a computer.\n§7§61§7 unit of field strength can store §61L§7 of condensate, and consumes §61§7 EU/t.\n§7When multiple containment fields are present on a network, injected condensate is split based on their capacities.\n§7§8§m-----------------------------------------§8§7\n§7Excess condensate can be inserted into the containment field, but it will quickly be §c§nvoided§c§7.\n§7When a containment field is overfilled, §c§n11%§c§7 of its condensate is deleted each second.\n§7If a containment field shuts down at any point, its contents will be §c§nvoided§c§7.\n§7§8§m-----------------------------------------§8§7\n§7The §6Bose-Einstein Condensate Detector Hatch§6§7 can be used to detect stored condensate levels.\n§aSupports TecTech Multi-Amp and Laser Hatches!\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines\nAdded by: §a§9Recursive Pineapple§r§7
