gt.blockmachines.multimachine.em.switch.adv.tooltip=Machine Type: §eComputation Network Switch, CNS§r\nVariable-length version of the Weighted Network Switch.\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nConsumes §b524,288§7 EU/t per middle slice while active.\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nComputation output is configured by right clicking transmission connectors with a screwdriver.\nTransmission connectors must be part of the structure for them to be configurable.\nComputation output for a hatch is directly controlled by the hatch's setting.\nFor weighted computation distribution, use the §6Weighted Network Switch With QoS§r.\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§aSupports TecTech Multi-Amp and Laser Hatches!\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.em.switch.adv.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §63§7x§63§7x§63-18§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front center\n§6   0x§7 - §680x §r§7Computer Casing\n§6   1x§7 - §681x §r§7Advanced Computer Casing\n§f   Energy Hatch: §7Any Computer Casing (Hint: 1)\n§f   Dynamo Hatch: §7Any Computer Casing (Hint: 1)\n§f   Multi-Amp Energy Hatch: §7Any Computer Casing (Hint: 1)\n§f   Laser Target Hatch: §7Any Computer Casing (Hint: 1)\n§f   Multi-Amp Dynamo Hatch: §7Any Computer Casing (Hint: 1)\n§f   Laser Source Hatch: §7Any Computer Casing (Hint: 1)\n§f   Data Reception Connector: §7Any Advanced Computer Casing (Hint: 2)\n§f   Data Transmission Connector: §7Any Computer Casing (Hint: 1)\n§f   Data Transmission Connector: §7Any Advanced Computer Casing (Hint: 2)\n   Uses sub channel §6length§r§7 for §6middle slice count\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.em.switch.tooltip=Machine Type: §eComputation Network Switch, CNS§r\nDistributes computation to transmission connectors based on weights.\nTransmission connectors are assigned an ID.\nScan connectors with a Portable Scanner to determine their ID.\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nComputation output is configured via TecTech parameters.\nThe first parameter in each group controls the hatch ID.\nThe second parameter in each group controls the hatch weight.\n§aSupports TecTech Multi-Amp and Laser Hatches!\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
