gt.blockmachines.multimachine.endothermichfridge.name=Endothermic Fridge
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.endothermichfridge.tooltip=Machine Type: §eVacuum Freezer, EnF, MVF§r\n§6256§7 Parallels\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nWhile active, the machine will cool down and increase its speed bonus up to §a1.5x\nTakes §d5 minutes§7 of constant running to reach maximum bonus\nWhile not running, the machine will return to normal temperatures\nOptionally supply §3250 mB§7/s of §bCryotheum§7 to speed up cooling by §95x\nThe drain rate of §bCryotheum§7 will increase §dlinearly§7 with the speed modifier\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nUpgrade to §dTier 2§7 to unlock §3Subspace Cooling\nWill further multiply §aspeed bonus §7by §6consuming §dexotic coolants:\n§620 L/s§7 : §a200% §7: §dMolten Infinity\n§620 L/s§7 : §a400% §7: §dMolten Spacetime\n§620 L/s§7 : §a800% §7: §dMolten Eternity\n§bCryotheum§7 drain rate is further multiplied by the §aspeed bonus\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§aSupports TecTech Multi-Amp and Laser Hatches!\nThis machine can run recipes regardless of tier, if given enough energy\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§o§b... without the other!\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines\nStructure by: §aPix3lated§r§7
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.endothermichfridge.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §623§7x§616§7x§623§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front center, 4th layer\n§6   750x §r§7Fridge Casing (minimum)\n§6   148x §r§7Tungstensteel Reinforced Block\n§6   148x §r§7Tungstensteel Pipe Casing\n§6   146x §r§7Callisto Ice Frame Box\n§6   135x §r§7Robust Tungstensteel Machine Casing\n§6   51x §r§7Coolant Duct\n§6   40x §r§7Ledox Sheetmetal\n§6   18x §r§7Any Tiered Glass\n   §9Tier 1 Structure:\n§6   351x §r§7Frost Proof Machine Casing\n   §9Tier 2 Structure:\n   §7Replace Frost Proof Machine Casing on\n   layers 1-3 with Infinity Cooled Casing\n§6   143x §r§7Frost Proof Machine Casing\n§6   208x §r§7Infinity Cooled Casing\n§f   Input Bus: §7Any Fridge Casing\n§f   Output Bus: §7Any Fridge Casing\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Any Fridge Casing\n§f   Output Hatch: §7Any Fridge Casing\n§f   Energy Hatch: §7Any Fridge Casing\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7Any Fridge Casing\n   Uses sub channel §6glass§r§7 for §6Glass Tier\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.engraver.name=Hyper-Intensity Laser Engraver
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.engraver.tooltip=Machine Type: §eLaser Engraver, HILE§r\n§a350%§7 Speed\n§b80%§7 EU Usage\nLaser source hatch determines maximum recipe tier and parallels\nRecipe tier and overclocks limited to laser source tier + 1\nWhen using a UEV+ laser source, one multi-amp energy hatch is allowed instead of regular energy hatches\nParallels equal to the cube root of laser source amperage input\nGlass tier determines maximum laser source tier\n§c§l§nUMV§7-tier glass accepts all laser source hatches\nUse screwdriver to disable laser rendering\nUse wire cutter to toggle realism mode if you hate angled lasers\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.engraver.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §65§7x§65§7x§65§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front bottom center\n§6   35x §r§7Laser Containment Casing (minimum)\n§6   9x §r§7Tungstensteel Frame Box\n§6   3x §r§7Any Tiered Glass (tiered)\n§f   Laser Resistant Plate: §7x1\n§f   Laser Source Hatch: §7x1\n§f   Input Bus: §7Any Casing\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Any Casing\n§f   Output Bus: §7Any Casing\n§f   Output Hatch: §7Any Casing\n§f   Energy Hatch: §7Any Casing\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7Any Casing\n   Uses sub channel §6glass§r§7 for §6Glass Tier\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.entitycrusher.name=Extreme Entity Crusher
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.entitycrusher.tooltip=Machine Type: §ePowered Spawner, EEC§r\nSpawns and kills monsters for you!\nProduces §a120 Liquid XP§7 per operation\nPowered Spawner goes in Controller Slot\nBase energy usage: §b1920§7 EU/t\nSupports §dperfect OC!\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHas a minimum recipe time of 20 ticks, further overclocks multiply outputs by 4x\nRecipe time is based on mob health\nYou can additionally put a weapon inside the GUI\nIt will speed up the process and apply the looting level from the weapon (maximum 4 levels)\nEnable Weapon Preservation to prevent the weapon from breaking on it's last hit\nEnable Weapon Cycling to pull a weapon from input when the current one breaks or is moved to an output\n§cEnchanting the spikes inside the structure does nothing!\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nIf the mob spawns §cinfernal§7, it will drain 8 times more power!\nYou can prevent §cinfernal§7 spawns by shift clicking with a screwdriver\nMobs who are always §cinfernal§7 will ignore this factor\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nYou can enable ritual mode with a screwdriver\nWhen in ritual mode, can link to above Well of Suffering rituals\nThe Ritual must be built directly centered above the machine\nWhen linked, mobs will start to buffer and die very slowly, providing blood to the linked altar\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nYou can disable mob animation with a soldering iron\nYou can enable batch mode with wire cutters. Providing §9 16x Time, Output, Weapon Damage\nEnergy Hatch limited by §fGlass§7 Tier, §2§nUV§7-tier unlocks all\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines\nAdded by: §a§4§lk§c§lu§6§lb§e§la§2§l6§a§l0§b§l0§3§l0§r§7
