gt.blockmachines.multimachine.oreprocessor.name=Integrated Ore Factory
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.oreprocessor.tooltip=Machine Type: §eOre Processor, IOF§r\n§4DEPRECATED - Controller will be removed in next major update!\n§4Check NEI for new Controller and conversion recipe\nDoes all ore processing in one step\n§61024§7 Parallels\nEvery ore costs 30EU/t, 2L lubricant, 200L distilled water\nRecipes that need extra input require their extra inputs on top of the normal costs\nProcessing time is dependent on mode\nUse a screwdriver to switch mode\nSneak click with screwdriver to void the stone dust\n§5200 §7Pollution per second\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§aOP stands for Ore Processor ;)\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.oreprocessor.tooltip.15564=Machine Type: §eOre Processor, IOF§r\nDoes all ore processing in one step\nParallel count scales with total input power: EU/t / 30\nEvery ore costs 30EU/t, 2L lubricant, 200L distilled water\nRecipes that need extra input require their extra inputs on top of the normal costs\nProcessing time is dependent on mode\nUse a screwdriver to switch mode\nSneak click with screwdriver to void the stone dust\n§aSupports TecTech Multi-Amp and Laser Hatches!\n§5200 §7Pollution per second\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§aOP stands for Ore Processor ;)\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines\nStructure by: §a§6Bavib§r§7
