gt.blockmachines.multimachine.purificationunitextractor.name=Absolute Baryonic Perfection Purification Unit
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.purificationunitextractor.tooltip=Machine Type: §ePurification Unit§r\n§b§lWater Tier: §f8§r\nMust be linked to a Purification Plant using a data stick to work\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nInsert §fQuark Releasing Catalysts §7into the input bus while running\nEvery recipe cycle, a different combination of §c2§7 different §fQuark Releasing Catalysts\nwill correctly identify the lone quark and succeed the recipe\nThe order of catalysts in the combination does not matter, so §9Up§7/§dDown§7 can be identified by inserting §dDown§7/§9Up\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nEvery §c20§7 ticks, consumes ALL catalysts in the input bus\nThe base cost of inserting a catalyst is §c144L§f Molten Infinity\nFor every duplicate occurrence of an inserted catalyst in the sequence, this cost is doubled\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nKeeps track of the entire sequence of catalysts inserted this recipe\nIf the correct catalyst combination is in the sequence of inserted catalysts, immediately outputs §c2000L §fStabilised Baryonic Matter\nAt the end of a successful recipe, outputs additional §c500L §fStabilised Baryonic Matter§7 per parallel\nAt the end of the recipe, returns all incorrectly inserted catalysts in the output bus\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§b§oThe final stage of water purification goes beyond subatomic particles and identifies the smallest\n§b§opossible imperfections within the baryons themselves. By correctly identifying which pairs of quark\n§b§oflavors are required, the unit will activate the catalysts, stabilizing the errant particles\n§b§oThis ultimately creates both Stabilised Baryonic Matter and, most importantly, absolutely perfectly purified water.\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.purificationunitextractor.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §617§7x§617§7x§617§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front center\n§6   300x §r§7Quark Exclusion Casing (minimum)\n§6   96x §r§7Femtometer-Calibrated Particle Beam Casing\n§6   37x §r§7Particle Beam Guidance Pipe Casing\n§6   240x §r§7Non-Photonic Matter Exclusion Glass\n§6   108x §r§7Bedrockium Frame Box\n§f   Input Bus: §7Any Quark Exclusion Casing. Stocking bus is blacklisted.\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Any Quark Exclusion Casing\n§f   Output Bus: §7Any Quark Exclusion Casing\n§f   Output Hatch: §7Any Quark Exclusion Casing\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.purificationunitflocculator.name=Flocculation Purification Unit
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.purificationunitflocculator.tooltip=Machine Type: §ePurification Unit§r\n§b§lWater Tier: §f3§r\nMust be linked to a Purification Plant using a data stick to work\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nSupply with §f%s§7 to operate\nOutputs §f%s§7 that can be recycled\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nDuring operation, will consume ALL §f%s§7 in the input hatch\nAt the end of the recipe, for every §c100000L §7of §f%s§7 consumed\ngain an additive §c10.0%%§7 increase to success. If total fluid supplied is not\na multiple of §c100000L§7, a penalty to success is applied using the following formula:\n§aSuccess = Success * 2^(-10 * Overflow ratio)\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§b§oStep three in purifying water is to remove microscopic contaminants such as dusts, microplastics and other\n§b§opollutants using a clarifying agent (In this case, polyaluminium chloride) to cause flocculation - the process\n§b§oof aggregating dispersed suspended particles from a solution into larger clumps for further filtration.\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.purificationunitflocculator.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §69§7x§65§7x§68§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front center\n§6   56x§7 - §665x §r§7Slick Sterile Flocculation Casing\n§6   30x §r§7Sterile Water Plant Casing\n§6   16x §r§7Reinforced Sterile Water Plant Casing\n§6   6x §r§7Tinted Industrial Glass\n§6   12x §r§7Adamantium Frame Box\n§6   9x §r§7Filter Machine Casing\n§f   Output Bus: §7§61§7+\n§f   Input Hatch: §7§61§7-§63\n§f   Output Hatch: §7§61§7-§63\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.purificationunitozonation.name=Ozonation Purification Unit
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.purificationunitozonation.tooltip=Machine Type: §ePurification Unit§r\n§b§lWater Tier: §f2§r\nMust be linked to a Purification Plant using a data stick to work\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nWill explode if the input hatch contains more than §c1024000L §fOzone Gas\nReceives a §c20%§7 bonus to success chance for every doubling of §fOzone Gas\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§b§oThe second step in water purification is ozonation, which involves injecting large quantities of small\n§b§obubbles of highly reactive ozone gas into the water. This removes trace element contaminants like\n§b§osulfur, iron and manganese, creating insoluble oxide compounds which are then filtered out.\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.purificationunitozonation.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §69§7x§610§7x§65§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front bottom center\n§6   96x§7 - §6102x §r§7Inert Filtration Casing\n§6   28x §r§7Reactive Gas Containment Casing\n§6   9x §r§7Any Tinted Industrial Glass\n§6   6x §r§7Tungstensteel Frame Box\n§6   3x §r§7PTFE Pipe Casing\n§f   Output Bus: §7§61§7+\n§f   Input Hatch: §7§61§7+\n§f   Output Hatch: §7§61§7+\n§f   Input Hatch (Ozone): §7§61\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.purificationunitphadjustment.name=pH Neutralization Purification Unit
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.purificationunitphadjustment.tooltip=Machine Type: §ePurification Unit§r\n§b§lWater Tier: §f4§r\nMust be linked to a Purification Plant using a data stick to work\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nInitial pH value every cycle varies from §c4.5§7 - §c9.5 pH\nIf the pH value is within §c0.05 pH §7of 7.0 pH at the end of the cycle, the recipe always succeeds\nOtherwise, the recipe always fails\nUse a pH Sensor Hatch to read the current pH value\nFor safety, the machine will shut down if the pH goes below 0 or exceeds 14\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nEvery §c20§7 ticks, consumes ALL §f%s§7 and §f%s§7 in the special hatches\n§cRaises §7the pH value by §c0.01 pH §7per piece of §fSodium Hydroxide Dust\n§cLowers §7the pH value by §c0.01 pH §7per §c10L §7of §fHydrochloric Acid\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§b§oThe fourth step of water purification is to neutralize the solution and bring its pH to exactly 7, rendering\n§b§othe solution inert with no hydrogen ion activity beyond water’s natural amphiproticity. Acids and bases from soils\n§b§oand geology cause natural alkalinity variations in water which can cause corrosive reactions with sensitive\n§b§omaterials. This necessitates the use of the corresponding neutralizing agents to pH balance the water.\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.purificationunitphadjustment.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §615§7x§66§7x§65§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front center\n§6   16x §r§7Stabilized Naquadah Water Plant Casing\n§6   18x §r§7Chemical Grade Glass\n§6   48x §r§7Naquadah Alloy Frame Box\n§6   134x §r§7Inert Neutralization Water Plant Casing\n§f   Input Hatch (Water): §7§61+\n§f   Output Hatch: §7§61\n§f   pH Sensor Hatch: §7§61-2\n§f   Input Bus (Sodium Hydroxide): §7§61\n§f   Input Hatch (Hydrochloric Acid): §7§61\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.purificationunitplasmaheater.name=Extreme Temperature Fluctuation Purification Unit
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.purificationunitplasmaheater.tooltip=Machine Type: §ePurification Unit§r\n§b§lWater Tier: §f5§r\nMust be linked to a Purification Plant using a data stick to work\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nComplete heating cycles by first heating the water to §c10000K§7,\nand then cooling it back down to §c0K\nInitial temperature is reset to §c0K§7 on recipe start\nEach completed heating cycle boosts success chance by §c33%\nIf the temperature ever reaches §c12500K§7 the recipe will fail and output steam\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nConsumes up to §c10L/s §fHelium Plasma§7 and up to §c100L/s §fSuper Coolant\n§cRaises §7the temperature by §c100K§7 per liter of plasma consumed\n§cLowers §7the temperature by §c5K§7 per liter of coolant consumed\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§b§oStep five of water purification is to evaporate complex organic polymers and extremophile organisms\n§b§othat might be resistant to simple acids, clarifying agents, and filters. Using an ultra high\n§b§opressure chamber in combination with extreme temperature fluctuations allows the water to remain\n§b§osupercritical while evaporating any remaining contaminants, ready for filtration\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.purificationunitplasmaheater.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §623§7x§615§7x§615§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front bottom center\n§6   669x §r§7Reinforced Sterile Water Plant Casing\n§6   54x §r§7Heat-Resistant Trinium Plated Casing\n§6   64x §r§7Any Tinted Industrial Glass\n§6   40x §r§7Superconductor Base ZPM Frame Box\n§6   8x §r§7Any Neonite\n§6   9x §r§7Superconducting Coil Block\n§f   Input Hatch (Water): §7§61+\n§f   Output Hatch: §7§61\n§f   Input Hatch (Coolant): §7§61\n§f   Input Hatch (Plasma): §7§61\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.purificationunituvtreatment.name=High Energy Laser Purification Unit
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.purificationunituvtreatment.tooltip=Machine Type: §ePurification Unit§r\n§b§lWater Tier: §f6§r\nMust be linked to a Purification Plant using a data stick to work\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nDuring operation, swap the lens in the §fLens Housing\nThe multiblock will output a signal through the §fLens Indicator Hatch\nwhen the current lens must be swapped\nLens swaps will be requested in random intervals of §c3 to 15s\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nSuccess chance is boosted by §c10.0% §7for each successful swap performed.\nRemoving a lens too early will fail the recipe\nFind the order of lenses in the recipe in NEI,\nor use a portable scanner to view the currently requested lens\nThe recipe always starts at the Orundum Lens\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§b§oThe sixth step of water purification involves identifying any remaining negatively charged ions within\n§b§othe water which may cause electrical faults in future wafer manufacturing. Bombarding the water with varying\n§b§owavelengths of photon beams will impart energy into outer-shell electrons, causing them to detach from the\n§b§oatoms themselves and pass through the walls of the tank, ensuring the water is perfectly electrically polar.\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.purificationunituvtreatment.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §613§7x§69§7x§69§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) §c(Hollow)\n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front bottom center\n§6   147x§7 - §6155x §r§7Naquadria-Reinforced Water Plant Casing\n§6   144x §r§7Electron-Permeable Neutronium Coated Glass\n§6   29x §r§7High Energy Ultraviolet Emitter Casing\n§6   56x §r§7Stellar Alloy Frame Box\n§f   Input Hatch, Output Hatch: §7§61+\n§f   Lens Housing: §7§61\n§f   Lens Indicator: §7§61\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
