gt.blockmachines.multimachine.supercapacitor.name=Lapotronic Supercapacitor
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.supercapacitor.tooltip=Machine Type: §eEnergy Storage, LSC§r\nLoses energy equal to 1% of the total capacity every 24 hours\nCapped at §c1,000,000§7 EU/t passive loss per §4§nUHV§7 capacitor\nThe passive loss increases §4100§7-fold for every capacitor tier above\nPassive loss is multiplied by the number of maintenance issues present\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nGlass shell has to be Tier - 3 of the highest capacitor tier\n§aSupports TecTech Multi-Amp and Laser Hatches!\n§2§nUV§7-tier §fGlass§7 required for §9Tec§1Tech§7 Laser Hatches\nAdd more or better capacitors to increase capacity\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nWireless mode can be enabled by right clicking with a screwdriver\nThis mode can only be enabled if you have a §4§nUHV§7+ capacitor in the multiblock.\nWhen enabled every §96,000§7 ticks the LSC will attempt to re-balance against your\nwireless EU network.\nIf there is less than §c6e13§7(§4§nUHV§7) EU in the LSC\nit will withdraw from the network and add to the LSC.\nIf there is more it will add §4§l§nall excess§r§7 EU to the network, removing it from the LSC\nThis can potentially brick your base, be careful\nThe threshold increases §4100§7-fold for every capacitor tier above\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.supercapacitor.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §65§7x§64-50§7x§65§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   Modular height of 4-50 blocks.\n   §fController: §7Front bottom center\n§f   Lapotronic Super Capacitor Casing: §75x2x5 base (at least 17x)\n§f   Lapotronic Capacitor (§8EV§7-§2§nUV§7), Ultimate Capacitor (§4§nUHV§7-§c§l§nUMV§7): §7Center 3x(1-47)x3 above base (9-423 blocks)\n   You can also use the Empty Capacitor to save materials if you use it for less than half the blocks\n§6   41x§7 - §6777x §r§7Any Tiered Glass (tiered)\n§f   Energy Hatch: §7Any Casing\n§f   Dynamo Hatch: §7Any Casing\n§f   Laser Target/Source Hatches: §7Any Casing, must be using §2§nUV§7-tier glass\n   You can have several I/O Hatches\n   Uses sub channel §6glass§r§7 for §6Glass Tier\n   Uses sub channel §6capacitor§r§7 for §6Capacitor Tier if specified. Otherwise pick any acceptable capacitor.\n   Uses sub channel §6height§r§7 for §6Structure Height\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7Any Casing\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.tfft.name=T.F.F.T
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.tfft.tooltip=Machine Type: §eFluid Tank§r\nHigh-Tech fluid tank that can hold up to 25 different fluids!\nHas 1/25th of the total capacity as capacity for each fluid\nRight clicking the controller with a screwdriver will turn on excess voiding\nFluid storage amount and running cost depends on the Storage Field Block used\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nNote on hatch locking:\nUse an Integrated Circuit in the GUI slot to limit which fluid is output\nThe index of a stored fluid can be obtained through the Tricorder\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.tfft.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §65§7x§65-15§7x§65§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front center\n§6   20x §r§7T.F.F.T Casing (minimum)\n§6   7x§7 - §6117x §r§7Storage Field Block (tiered)\n   Energy hatch is not required when running cost is 0\n§6   48x§7 - §6208x §r§7Any Tiered Glass (EV+)\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7Any top or bottom Casing\n§f   Energy Hatch: §7Any top or bottom Casing\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Instead of any casing or glass, has to touch Storage Field Block\n§f   Output Hatch: §7Instead of any casing or glass, has to touch Storage Field Block\n   You can have a bunch of hatches\n§f   Multi I/O Hatches: §7Instead of any casing or glass, has to touch Storage Field Block\n   Use MIOH with conduits or fluid storage buses to see all fluids at once.\n   Uses sub channel §6glass§r§7 for §6Glass Tier\n   Uses sub channel §6field§r§7 for §6Storage Field Tier\n   Uses sub channel §6height§r§7 for §6Structure Height\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
gt.blockmachines.multimachine.tm.microwave.tooltip=Machine Type: §eMicrowave Grinder§r\nController block of the Microwave Grinder\nStarts a timer when enabled\nWhile the timer is running anything inside the machine will take damage\nThe machine will also collect any items inside of it\nCan be configured with a Parametrizer\n(Do not insert a Wither)\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
