gt.blockmachines.quantumforcetransformer.controller.tier.single.name=Quantum Force Transformer
gt.blockmachines.quantumforcetransformer.controller.tier.single.tooltip=Machine Type: §eQuantum Force Transformer, QFT§r\nAllows Complex processing lines to be performed instantly in one step\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§dPulse Manipulator§7 Tier determines maximum recipe tier\nEvery recipe requires a specific §dcatalyst§7\n§dCatalysts§7 have to be placed in a Bulk Catalyst Housing\nGains §61§7 Parallel per §dCatalyst§7\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§aShielding Core§7 Tier determines §aFocusing§7 Bonuses\nPut a circuit in the controller to specify the focused output, based on NEI order\nIf Input Separation is on: put the circuit in the circuit slot of the bus\nConsumes 4 * §aFocus Tier§7 * sqrt(§6parallels§7) L §9Neptunium Plasma§7 to §afocus§7\nThe better the §aFocus Tier§7, the §astronger§7 the effect\n§aFocused§7 Output will have its §bprobability boosted§7, with other output's being reduced evenly by the total boost\nConsumes 4 * §aFocus Tier§7 * sqrt(§6parallels§7) L §2Fermium Plasma§7 to §2boost all outputs\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nUse a screwdriver to enable §9Fluid mode\nFluid mode turns all possible outputs into their fluid variant, if avaliable\nThis machine can run recipes regardless of tier, if given enough energy\n§aSupports TecTech Multi-Amp and Laser Hatches!\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines\nAdded by: §a§9§lBlue§b§lWeabo§r§7 & §a§aSteelux§r§7
