gt.blockmachines.solartower.controller.tier.single.name=Solar Tower
gt.blockmachines.solartower.controller.tier.single.tooltip=Machine Type: §eSolar Tower§r\nContributing Green Energy towards the future\nSurround with rings of Solar Reflectors\nThe Reflectors increase the internal heat value of the Tower (see below for formula)\nEach Reflector ring increases tier, the first ring is required for the Tower to work\nInput: Solar Salt (Cold)\nOutput: Solar Salt (Hot)\nEvery cycle (10 seconds), heat increases and all the Cold Solar Salt is heated\nConverting Cold to Hot Solar Salt reduces heat, equal to the amount converted\nThis conversion only happens if heat >= 30000 and controller efficiency = 100%\nIf there's more Cold Salt than heat, all the heat is used up and returns to 0\nThe heat increase is most efficient at exactly half of maximum heat\nMinimum efficiency at 0 or 100000 heat, maximum efficiency at 50000\nHeat Efficiency formula: ( 7000 - [|currentHeat - 50000| ^ 0.8]) / 7000\nHeat gain per cycle: numberHeaters * heatEfficiency * (10 + bonus)\nBonus: 1 ring  = +1, 2 rings = +2, 3 rings = +4, 4 rings = +8, 5 rings = +16\nTotal number of reflectors based on how many rings are built:\n1 ring = 36, 2 rings = 88, 3 rings = 156, 4 rings = 240, 5 rings = 340\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
gt.blockmachines.solartower.controller.tier.single.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §615-31§7x§628§7x§615-31§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Top center\n§6   229x §r§7Structural Solar Casing (minimum)\n§6   60x §r§7Thermally Insulated Casing (minimum)\n§6   66x §r§7Salt Containment Casing (minimum)\n§6   60x §r§7Thermal Containment Casing (minimum)\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Hint block number 2 (Min 1)\n§f   Output Hatch: §7Hint block number 2 (Min 1)\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7Hint block number 2\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
gt.blockmachines.source_chamber.name=Source Chamber
gt.blockmachines.source_chamber.tooltip=Machine Type: §eParticle Source§r\nGenerates particle beams from specific §dsource materials\nUse a §bportable scanner §7for info about the input/output of this multiblock\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nNEI has the list of §dsource materials§7 and their stats\nRecipes are all one second long and output a single beam packet\nIncreasing the power above the §3EU/t Required§7 asymptotically approaches the §dMax Material Energy\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nParticle beams have a §5particle type§7, §9energy§7, §2focus§7, and §6rate\n§5Type§7 determines the charge, rest mass, and §9Max Particle Energy\n§9Energy§7 is the energy of the particle beam in electron volts (eV)\n§2Focus§7 is the width of the particle beam\n§6Rate§7 is the amount of particles per packet\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§9Output Beam Energy§7 = min(§9Max Particle Energy§7, §eaeV§f)\nwhere §eaeV§f = §dMax Material Energy§f * (1 - 1.001^(§9-Energy Ratio§f * (§3EU/t Provided§f - §3EU/t Required§f)))\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
gt.blockmachines.source_chamber.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §65§7x§65§7x§66§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) §c(Hollow)\n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front bottom center\n§6   56x §r§7Shielded Accelerator Casing\n§6   52x §r§7Shielded Accelerator Glass\n§6   16x §r§7Electrode Casing\n§f   Beam Output Hatch: §7Hint block with number 4\n§f   Energy Hatch: §7Hint block with number 3\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7Hint block with number 3\n§f   Input Bus: §7Hint block with number 1\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Hint block with number 1\n§f   Output Bus: §7Hint block with number 2\n   §cRequires 1 input bus OR 1 input hatch\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
gt.blockmachines.spaceelevator.name=Space Elevator
gt.blockmachines.spaceelevator.tooltip=Machine Type: §eSpace Elevator§r\n§o%s\nCan be equipped with up to §a12 §7Space Elevator Modules\nMotor tier limits module tier and amount of possible modules\nEach module has its own space for IO, except energy\nEnergy is supplied to this controller and gets distributed\nStarting from §dMotor MK-III §7the structure can be expanded to fit §a24 §7modules\nMax module amount is §a6§7/§912§7/§d15§7/§618§7/§c24§7 for §aMK-I§7/§9MK-II§7/§dMK-III§7/§6MK-IV§7/§cMK-V§7 motors correspondingly\nDisabling this controller also pauses all modules\n§aSupports TecTech Multi-Amp and Laser Hatches!\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines\nAdded by: §a§9§dminecraft7771§r§7
